==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Medieval Latin < Arabic {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} (''wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing), from the expression
{{ARchar|[[نسر|النسر]]) [[واقع|الواقع]]}}, ''(an-nasr al-wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing [[eagle]]). The active participle {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} derives from the verb {{ARchar|[[وقع]]}} (''wáqa‘a'', to fall, to drop, to tumble, to alight, to pounce).

====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia}}
'''Vega'''

#{{Astronomy}} the brightest [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Lyra]].

===Etymology 2===
From Spanish [[vega]] ([[meadow]], fertile [[lowland]]) from the pre-Roman [[w:Iberian language|Iberian]] language.

====Proper noun====
'''Vega''' (''plural:'' [[Vegas]])

# Hispanic surname and placename, usually preceded by [[la#Spanish|la]] or ''de la'' in the singular, or by [[las#Spanish|las]] or ''de las'' in the plural (e.g., [[Las Vegas]]).


